  {panel}

The ability to clone a users rights, space permissions etc with all it's groups  and system permissions to antother already existing user would be highly appreciated.

We have this problem since our users are created via LDAP, so I did not find a way yet, and oftern developers leave the compnay and someone else should take all their resposonibities and there fore would need the exact same rights (added to their alrdy existing ones).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45639].
  {panel}

As requested on [Twitter|https://twitter.com/AlexPasternak/status/809853578097623040], I'd like a way to disable the built-in Find in Confluence. It is slow to launch and process, and takes up too much space. When just searching for text, I'd much rather just use the built-in browser find.

I typically hit Cmd-F, and start typing, but because it takes so long to come up, you actually type the text you want to search for into the page you're editing. So you have to train yourself to hit Cmd-F, but wait. With the built-in browser find, that is not necessary.

Search and replace is a rare function and I'm fine to launch it another way, or even without a keyboard shortcut. This should not own Cmd-F. Please make this be a user preference at least, thanks.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45637].
  {panel}

I'd like to browse pages by hierarchy, e.g. with cursor keys. This would be a very nice feature for quick reviews. Of cource you can export, but that's sometimes to much.

I see, that this could cause load on the server, so perhaps this should be optional.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45624].
  {panel}

I often need to edit and align page properties across several pages and it would be much easer if I could edit these within the properties report and have the changes then posted in the corresponding page

