*Background of the Request*

Currently, if a page or space export failed or hang user cannot cancel the process. They need to contact the support team to restart their instance in order to kill the hang pdf export process.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45590].
  {panel}

At https://confluence.atlassian.com/conf59/getting-help-and-support-792499898.html?_ga=1.15768629.287511926.1470356386

there are two sections titled Features and bugs which is confusing

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45588].
  {panel}

Sometimes when many users has edited a Confluence page at the same time, after saving we found that the changes we have made disappear.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45585].
  {panel}

I would like to see a feature where Users added to a Confluence space restriction role (i.e. Can View & Edit) automatically get added to a Jira project role. 

There would have to be some configuration that would allow me to map a Confluence space/role to a Jira Project & Role so this could be customized. 

This would allow for easier management of Project tooling access as I would only need to add users in one spot as opposed to two.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45579].
  {panel}

The LDAP config options allow you to set a name (firstnameAttribute and surnameAttribute) for a person, then separately assign the unique identifier for that person (usernameAttribute).

Currently the group options only allow a single field (groupnameAttribute) for both these options, meaning if your groups are named after internal department codes these are displayed whenever you use the groups inside Confluence.

It would be great to have two configurable fields which allows the unique id of the group to be different from the displayed name.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45573].
  {panel}

A lot of customer confusion over whether attachments are included in XML space exports.  https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Exporting+Confluence+Pages+and+Spaces+to+XML?focusedCommentId=641663205#comment-641663205

The description on the  Full Export option is misleading, and says:

{quote}Generates a XML file for each page in this space, including those not visible to you, and excluding blogs, comments, and attachments.{quote}

This has led customers to believe that attachments are not included, when they are. 

I've drafted some new text for the page below:

{panel}
Full Export
Generates an XML file containing all pages in the space, including those not visible to you. 
Custom Export
Generates an XML file containing only selected pages.
{panel}

Also, when logged in with Confluence administrator permissions (not a member of the confluence-administrator group), you see this message 

{panel} Export the space to a zipped XML file. You can import the XML file into earlier Confluence versions from 5.3 to 5.7-m15, and into compatible later versions. When importing, please refer to the compatibility information on your Confluence Backup & Restore administration page. {panel}

It contains a link that is only accessible to Sysadmins - I think this text is meant to only appear when someone has System Administrator permissions.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45547].
  {panel}

The deprecated Office Connector allows users to display files and documents inline, which means that users can read documents in context with the rest of the page.

With the new files preview in 5.7, using the new files experience forces files to be opened in a lightbox, which means it's impossible to view the rest of the page and the files at the same time.

We should provide the option to display the files experience in line. This is particularly important for complex documents that _do not render_ in the Office Connector (and since the Office Connector is deprecated, display bugs won't be fixed because the Files experience renders them correctly).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45545].
  {panel}

