{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45544].
  {panel}

The new dashboard (introduced in Confluence 5.9) is dead amaze and a massive improvement, but it would really nice to have the ability to filter the content that gets displayed, e.g. show only blogs, or pages, or questions. This preference could be persisted in e.g. local browser storage

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45539].
  {panel}

We are using the plug-in "SubSpace Navigation for Confluence". In former versions there was a macro to list all SubSpaces in a space. We found that very helpful. So a re-launch of this macro would be very useful for us.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45535].
  {panel}

We have such a wide range of spaces applicable to different groups, teams, and locations (almost 200 spaces). Our users either have to subscribe to all blog posts (which often means they are receiving a lot of unnecessary email notifications and getting frustrated) or they are going to many spaces one at a time to watch each individual blog. It would be really helpful for there to be a quick way for them to choose which space blogs are applicable to them. The Space Directory seems like a great place for them to be able to go down the list and quickly choose which space blogs they are interested in. Perhaps if they could even choose an entire category with one click, that would be really nice. I think this is a feature that would make our users extremely happy. Thank you!

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45510].
  {panel}

There are cases where malformed revisions have been set on content entities in production environments. We will put validation on this property to prevent this from happening in the future, and where the problem already exists repair the issue on the entity.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45508].
  {panel}

It would be helpful if users were able to unwatch Calendars which are within pages, without unwatching the whole page. 

The thing is, users don't want to receive e-mails for each change in calendars but they still want to receive notifications from other changes in the page.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45499].
  {panel}

I like giving the quick summary when I update a page, e.g. "Making some changes after talking to Team Y", which helps make it clear what's going on. It would be helpful to be able to mention someone in that comment to basically share the page with them. Something like "Making some changes after talking to Team Y. @JDoe, can you take a look"? This would help users elevate certain page updats about others where it's most important for them to engage.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45498].
  {panel}

This is similar to https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-18153 in that my goal is to be able to be able to filter the Confluence updates based on how important it is. Right now, updates are Created, Updated, or Commented (More or less). Particularly on comments, it would be helpful to be able to distinguish between comments on a page I wrote or in direct response to one of my comments as compared to a comment on a page in a space I'm watching wholly. I'm sure there are more granular levels, but having the emails say "There is one new comment on a page you wrote" or "John Smith responded to your comment" or "There is one new comment on a page in a space you're watching" would be helpful for triaging.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45491].
  {panel}

Confluence Space import allows the user to upload files that are not valid, for example, Spaces that were exported from a lower version or wrong file formats. 

The error informing the backup was invalid appears only after upload is completed and the user clicks on Import. 

It would be better if the upload of spaces from lower versions or wrong file format was not allowed. Also, an error message should be shown when a user tries to upload a wrong file to Space Import.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45481].
  {panel}

h4. For now, anyone who experience this issue, open a ticket in our cloud support so we can apply the fix in the affected database (cloud instance).
h4. Summary

The table 'AO_7CDE43_NOTIFICATION' has another identity column: {{SCHEME_ID}} in Confluence Cloud which is *non-existent* in server instances and other cloud instances of the same version (still need to investigate the reason for this column). 

The restore will read a SQL statement that is unacceptable for *ms sql server*:
{code:java}
Caused by: com.atlassian.activeobjects.spi.ActiveObjectsImportExportException: There was an error during import/export with plugin Atlassian Notifications SPI Plugin(com.atlassian.plugin.notifications.notifications-module) #3.3.3 (table AO_7CDE43_NOTIFICATION):Error executing update for SQL statement 'CREATE TABLE AO_7CDE43_NOTIFICATION (
    ID INTEGER IDENTITY(1,1),
    NOTIFICATION_SCHEME_ID INTEGER,
    SCHEME_ID INTEGER IDENTITY(1,1),
CONSTRAINT pk_AO_7CDE43_NOTIFICATION_ID PRIMARY KEY(ID)
)'
{code}
And will fail with:
{code:java}
Caused by: java.sql.SQLException: Multiple identity columns specified for table 'AO_7CDE43_NOTIFICATION'. Only one identity column per table is allowed.
{code}
The restore will read a SQL statement that is unacceptable for *MySQL Server* as well:
{code:java}
Caused by: com.atlassian.activeobjects.spi.ActiveObjectsImportExportException: There was an error during import/export with plugin Atlassian Notifications SPI Plugin(com.atlassian.plugin.notifications.notifications-module) #3.3.3 (table AO_7CDE43_NOTIFICATION):Error executing update for SQL statement 'CREATE TABLE AO_7CDE43_NOTIFICATION (
    ID INTEGER AUTO_INCREMENT,
    NOTIFICATION_SCHEME_ID INTEGER,
    SCHEME_ID INTEGER AUTO_INCREMENT,
    PRIMARY KEY(ID)
) ENGINE=InnoDB'
{code}
{code:java}
Caused by: com.mysql.jdbc.exceptions.jdbc4.MySQLSyntaxErrorException: Incorrect table definition; there can be only one auto column and it must be defined as a key
{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45479].
  {panel}

The space trees on the sidebar be set to "stick", so as to keep them from contracting and expanding when working in a space. Possible to have it show the full tree of the space no matter what page you are on.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45477].
  {panel}

h3. Summary

When generation a backup, it fails with:
{code:java}
2016-12-01 08:48:13.581535500 Caused by: com.atlassian.rdbms.dbimportexport.dbie.api.datafile.DatafileParseException: Could not parse timestamp '2016-10-17 11:59:46.178' with pattern '(ParseCaseSensitive(false)Value(YearOfEra,4,10,NEVER)'-'Value(MonthOfYear,2)'-'Value(DayOfMonth,2))' '(Value(HourOfDay,2)':'Value(MinuteOfHour,2)':'Value(SecondOfMinute,2)[Fraction(MicroOfSecond,0,6,DecimalPoint)])[Offset(+HH:MM:SS,'+00')][Offset(+HH:MM,'+00')][Offset(+HH,'+00')]Text(Era)'{code}
 

The backup fails to parse the date in the AO table:
{code:java}
"AO_6D345F_CUSTOM_LIBRARY"{code}
Which holds custom libraries from Gliffy.
h3. Enviroment

Confluence Cloud = 1000.607.0
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Generate a backup through the Backup Manager

h3. Expected Results

Backup gets created successfully.
h3. Actual Results

Backups fails with:
{code:java}
Export error Unsupported field: InstantSeconds But don't worry, we'll fix it for you! You just need to contact Atlassian support and paste in this error message, timestamp and your instance details. Timestamp: 2016-11-30T09:47:56.132-08:00{code}
 
h3. Workaround

There are two workarounds:
 # Wait until roughly the end of January, when we are migrating to a new version of Gliffy. After this, it should work again. Note that the new version of Gliffy does not support the import/export of custom shape libraries.

 - - OR -

 # Contact support who will run the Gliffy data fix script. (attached to ticket)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45476].
  {panel}

1)  The sort feature of this macro is shown in the header but it is not working. The result is always sorted by "Modified".

2) If my role is confluence_administrator, and there are results (pages having labels specified in this macro) which have access restricted to the author only, I cannot see such pages in the list. But I can see the same page in the page tree (left frame) and open it from there. So, this macro has a different implementation of the access verification than other macros.

 

Issue found in Confluence 5.8 and 5.10.  (Assume that 5.9 has the same issue)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45474].
  {panel}

Working at a company that uses their Confluence as a communication platform with clients (we have a Confluence Space per client), I would love to see which user opened the page and at what time in a Page's history. This way I can see if a client has looked at the documentation recently, have an idea of their level of involvement, and grasp how actively a page is used.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45462].
  {panel}

If the included page is deleted, rendering throws an error exception.

What i would want, the reference to included page should be cancelled automatically if the included page is deleted.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45461].
  {panel}

h3. Summary

 

User would like to have an option or macro that can list out all hyperlinks in their confluence.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45429].
  {panel}

Special characters e.g. "&" in Pagenames was not correctly encoded in the Page favorites list. 

